description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for a skilled and experienced nurse to join our clinical nurse specialist (CNS) team caring for adult patients with a diagnosis of either myeloma or lymphoma. As part of this team you would play a significant role in the patient’s care pathway, supporting patients through their treatment journey and wherever possible responding to patients holistic needs. This will include providing support for patients and families who are making decisions from diagnosis and throughout the cancer pathway. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The CNS team provides a regional service which includes the coordination of the autologous transplant service and deliver a number of nurse led services and clinics.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a senior nurse working independently but within a team environment, you will need to be a confident, outgoing person with excellent communication skills who will demonstrate an ability to be highly self-motivated. Significant background knowledge of haematological malignancies and a willingness to participate in professional development and develop further nurse led services are highly desirable. In-house training and education will be provided to develop and build on an existing knowledge base. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post is full time and permanent &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information please contact either &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gill Stewart (CNS Team Leader) on (0113) 2068353&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Andy Bennett (Matron) on (0113) 2068238&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
